            '**LM Studio is a desktop application for running local LLMs.** It provides a graphical model browser, a built-in chat interface, and a local API server вҖ” all in one app. Under the hood, it uses llama.cpp for inference, the same engine that powers [Ollama](/local-llms/how-to-install-ollama).',
            'The key difference from Ollama is that LM Studio is entirely GUI-driven. You browse and download models through the app interface, start chats with a click, and manage model settings with sliders rather than configuration files.',
