            'Base models (e.g., `llama3.1:8b`) are not fine-tuned for conversation and produce raw completions that look like garbled text when prompted with a question. Always use the instruct variant: `llama3.1:8b-instruct`. See [How to Install LM Studio](/local-llms/how-to-install-lm-studio) for the GUI-based approach to switching model variants.',
            'In Ollama, the default tag for most models already points to the instruct variant. If you downloaded from Hugging Face manually, confirm the filename includes "Instruct" or "chat".',
