            '**Q2_K vs FP16**: 15вҖ“25% degradation. Significant quality loss across all task types. Only use when RAM constraint is absolute.',
            '**Q8_0 vs FP16**: under 0.5% degradation вҖ” essentially identical for all practical purposes.',
            'The K_M variants (K-Quant Medium) use a mixed-precision approach that preserves quality better than older Q4_0 quantization at the same bit count. Always prefer Q4_K_M over Q4_0 when both are available.',
